pan><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">n 2012, there were 51,521 White British pupils</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">eligible for free school meals at the end of Key</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">Stage 4. This constitutes just under two thirds</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">(64%) of the total number of pupils elig</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">ible for</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">free school meals in the 2011/12 cohort.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="9" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 33.18pt; padding-left:2.82pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">The difference between the attainment of White British pupils from low income backgrounds and their more advantaged peers</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">i.e. </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">the attainment ‘gap’,</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> is much larger than for any of the other main ethnic gr</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">oups.</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> In 2012, for example, the ‘gap’ </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">at GCSE</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">between </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">White British pupils from low income backgrounds and their more advantaged White British peers was 32 percentage points compared with only 18 percentage points for Indian pupils and 6 percentage points for Bangladeshi pupils. </span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="10" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">In 2012, just over a third o</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">f pupils from low</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">income backgrounds (36%) left school with</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">five good GCSEs including English and maths</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">compared with over three-fifths of their better</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">off peers (63%).</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> However</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">, only 31</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">% of White British pupils from low income backgrounds attained the benc</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">hmark 5 good GCSEs compared with </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">40</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">% of disadvanta</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">ged Black Caribbean pupils, 48</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">% of disadvantag</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">ed Black African pupils and 59</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">% of disadvantaged Bangladeshi pupils.</span></