than </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">disadvantaged White British girls.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="19" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 36pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">The</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">poor performance of low income White British</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">pupils is not, therefore, a gender issue</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">It is crucial that we </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">solve the problem of low achievement by White British boys </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">and</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> girls from low income backgrounds</span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt"> if we are </span><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">to solve the problem of low achievement overall.</span></li></ol><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">What steps schools can take to improve the educational outcomes and attainment of white working class pupils</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><ol start="20" type="1" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="font-family:Tahoma; font-size:12pt; margin:0pt 0pt